<p>
 Suppose <m>f^\prime(x)=0</m> on the interval <m>(\alpha,\beta)</m> and
    that <m>a</m> and  <m>b</m> are two points in that interval.  Use an
    argument similar to the proof of the first derivative test to show
    that <m>f(a)=f(b)</m>.
  </p>
</statement>
</task>
<task>
<statement>
<p>
