<task>
<statement>
<p>
 Show that if <m>f^\prime(x)=g^\prime(x)</m> on the interval
    <m>(\alpha,\beta)</m>, then <me>f(x)=g(x)+c</me> for some constant <m>c</m>.
    \hint{Consider the function <m>F(x)=f(x)-g(x)</m>.}    
  </p>
</statement>
</task>
<task>
